                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Eat less   sugar:   NCP   editorial
                                              
	Mumbai/New Delhi, Feb. 7 (PTI): Sharad Pawars party has offered the country a remedy for the soaring sugar prices, along with some age-old medical advice for free  eat less of the sweetener and keep diabetes at bay.        
	No one dies due to not eating sugar. On the other hand, by eating items made from sugar, diabetes increases. So, it is not necessary that everyone consume sugar, said an editorial in the latest issue of Rashtravadi, the mouthpiece of Pawars Nationalist Congress Party (NCP), in response to criticism that the Union agriculture minister had failed to check the prices, hovering around Rs 50 a kg.        
	The magazines managing editor is Madhukar Pichad, the NCPs Maharashtra chief. It is edited by former journalist Sudhir Bhongale.         
	Pawars aides distanced the minister from the remarks.         
	The remark is his (Pichads) personal view. The NCP has nothing to do with it, spokesperson Gurunath Kulkarni said in Mumbai. But the BJP demanded an explanation, senior leader Rajiv Pratap Rudy said in Delhi.                                                                                                                                                           
